CAIRO: Egypt’s military has announced the launch of International Maritime Training Activities in the Red Sea, as part of its plan “to raise the level of training and exchange experiences with the armed forces of brotherly and friendly countries.” It said the training will last “several days,” with the participation of Egypt’s navy and the Western Joint Forces Command. The exercise includes training to confront atypical maritime threats, implementing maritime security measures, securing ships with important cargo, combating naval mines, training in command and control work, and medical training.